    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_002698_0001" n="0001"/> 
<lb/><opener><dateline rend="right"><placeName>R. Zambesi</placeName><date when="1862-03-04">4<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> March
<lb/>1862</date></dateline>
<lb/>
<lb/><salute>My Dear Sir</salute></opener>
<lb/><p>Many thanks
<lb/>for your kind attentions
<lb/>to <unclear>Mr. L v</unclear> self in finding
<lb/>the letters &amp; <unclear>newspapers</unclear>
<lb/>which came all safely
<lb/>to hand - The <term type="animal">mules</term> too
<lb/>were in excellent condition
<lb/>and seem fine strong
<lb/>animals - The carts &amp;
<lb/>harness all night - By the
<lb/>kind assistance of
<lb/><unclear>Captain</unclear> <persName>Wilson</persName> &amp;his <unclear>offians</unclear>
<lb/>we had the greater part
<lb/>of the hull put aboard
<lb/>the Pioneer but the
<lb/><geogName type="river">Zambesi</geogName> is in <unclear>mph</unclear><!-- seems like some kind of square cut glitch? I don't know. BL-->
<lb/>flood and more rapid
<lb/>then we ever saw it

	<pb facs="liv_002698_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>It is indeed far too strong
<lb/>a current for the Pioneer
<lb/>with 35 tons in her, so
<lb/>after spending 3 weeks in
<lb/>getting up to <settlement>Shupauga</settlement><!--I am not sure what this is, but I presume it is a village or town? BL-->
<lb/>we are obliged to unload -
<lb/>put the hull together &amp;
<lb/>tow her <hi rend="below">^</hi><hi rend="above">the new one</hi> up to the
<lb/>cataracts - this will detain
<lb/>us till may - </p>
<lb/><p>Seeing that we made
<lb/>such miserably slow
<lb/>progress Captain <persName>Wilson</persName>
<lb/>acceptedto the <unclear>vepuestro</unclear>
<lb/>Miss <persName>Mackenzie</persName> to see
<lb/>taken forview to the
<lb/>bishop in his gig - the
<lb/>bishop was not found
<lb/>at the <unclear>Rus</unclear> as he engaged

	<pb facs="liv_002698_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>to be and we hear by his
<lb/>return of one boat from
<lb/>Shine the Captain's new <unclear>gove</unclear>
<lb/>on it near the cataracts
<lb/>where he would send up
<lb/>for the bishop and deliver
<lb/>up his change - she
<lb/>is very weakly at best
<lb/>and was ill when they 
<lb/>were kept by the return
<lb/>boat. There is no doubt
<lb/>but Ladies would be
<lb/>a great boon to the
<lb/>mission if they were
<lb/>strong as Mrs. <persName>Burrays</persName>
<lb/>appears to be, but
<lb/>Miss <persName>Mackenzie</persName>'s is
<lb/>a peculiar case &amp;
<lb/>I have my fears

	<pb facs="liv_002698_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>Believe me
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>Dear Sir</p>

<lb/><closer rend="right"><salute>Most Truly yours</salute>
<lb/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed>
<lb/>
<lb/><del type="cancelled" hand="#DL">David Livingstone seems to have crossed out illegible writing</del> Esq.</closer>

